<h1 id="adding-state">Adding State</h1><p>So far our templates have been static. The <code>&lt;let></code> tag introduces state: a
value that can change over time, with every expression that uses it updating
automatically.</p>
<learn-checkpoint files=[{"path":"index.marko","content":"<let/volume=40>\n\n<label>\n  Volume\n  <input type=\"range\" min=0 max=100 value:parseFloat:=volume>\n</label>\n<p>${volume === 0 ? \"Muted\" : `Playing at ${volume}%`}</p>\n<button onClick() {\n  volume = 0;\n}>\n  Mute\n</button>\n"}] auto><app-code-block lang="marko" text="<let/volume=40>\n<label>\n  Volume${\" \"}\n  <input type=\"range\" min=0 max=100 value:parseFloat:=volume>\n</label>\n<p>${volume === 0 ? \"Muted\" : `Playing at ${volume}%`}</p>\n<button onClick() {\n  volume = 0;\n}>Mute</button>" markoAlts=["let/volume=40\nlabel\n  -- Volume${\" \"}\n  input type=\"range\" min=0 max=100 value:parseFloat:=volume\np -- ${volume === 0 ? \"Muted\" : `Playing at ${volume}%`}\nbutton onClick() {\n  volume = 0;\n} -- Mute","<let/volume=40>\n\n<label>\n  Volume\n  <input type=\"range\" min=0 max=100 value:parseFloat:=volume>\n</label>\n<p>${volume === 0 ? \"Muted\" : `Playing at ${volume}%`}</p>\n<button onClick() {\n  volume = 0;\n}>Mute</button>","let/volume=40\n\nlabel\n  -- Volume\n  input type=\"range\" min=0 max=100 value:parseFloat:=volume\np -- ${volume === 0 ? \"Muted\" : `Playing at ${volume}%`}\nbutton onClick() {\n  volume = 0;\n} -- Mute"]/></><p>Drag the slider in the preview. The <code>:=</code> shorthand keeps the input and the
<code>volume</code> variable in sync in both directions, and the <code>Mute</code> button assigns to
the same variable from an event handler.</p>
<p>There is no render function and no subscription to manage. The compiler sees
which expressions read <code>volume</code> and wires up exactly the updates needed.</p>
